{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-readme-js","path":"/joaomilho/awesome-idris/readme/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"91b3942e-874c-5823-b904-f2ceec305c72","html":"<h1 id=\"awesome-idris-awesome\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#awesome-idris-awesome\" aria-label=\"awesome idris awesome permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Awesome Idris <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome\"><img src=\"https://cdn.rawgit.com/sindresorhus/awesome/d7305f38d29fed78fa85652e3a63e154dd8e8829/media/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.idris-lang.org/\"><img src=\"https://www.idris-lang.org/logo/logo.png\" align=\"right\" width=\"160\"></a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>An auxiliary list of awesome <a href=\"https://www.idris-lang.org/\">Idris</a> resources.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Idris is a general purpose pure functional programming language with dependent types. Dependent types allow types to be predicated on values, meaning that some aspects of a program’s behaviour can be specified precisely in the type. It is compiled, with eager evaluation. Its features are influenced by Haskell and ML.</p>\n<h2 id=\"contents\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#contents\" aria-label=\"contents permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contents</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#official-resources\">Official resources</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#articles\">Articles</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#books\">Books</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#papers\">Papers</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#presentations\">Presentations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#projects\">Projects</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"official-resources\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#official-resources\" aria-label=\"official resources permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Official resources</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.idris-lang.org/\">Official website</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/idris-lang/Idris-dev\">Official repo</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/idris-lang/Idris-dev\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.3k</span></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"articles\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#articles\" aria-label=\"articles permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Articles</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://deque.blog/2017/06/14/10-things-idris-improved-over-haskell/\">10 things Idris improved over Haskell</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://crufter.com/idris-a-language-that-will-change-the-way-you-think-about-programming\">Meet Idris, a language that will change the way you think about programming</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://kevinmahoney.co.uk/articles/tests-vs-types/\">Tests vs. Types</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"books\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#books\" aria-label=\"books permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Books</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.manning.com/books/type-driven-development-with-idris\">Type Driven Development With Idris</a> - Most important book published so far.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.kent.ac.uk/people/staff/sjt/TTFP/\">Type Theory and Functional Programming</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cse.chalmers.se/research/group/logic/book/book.pdf\">Programming in Martin-Löf's Type Theory</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://idris-hackers.github.io/software-foundations/pdf/sf-idris-2018.pdf\">Software Foundations</a> - Repo is <a href=\"https://github.com/idris-hackers/software-foundations\">here</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/idris-hackers/software-foundations\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">388</span></span></a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://leanpub.com/gidti\">Gentle Introduction to Dependent Types with Idris</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"papers\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#papers\" aria-label=\"papers permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Papers</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://eb.host.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/drafts/elab-reflection.pdf\">Elaborator Reflection: Extending Idris in Idris</a> - David Christiansen and Edwin Brady, 2016.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://eb.host.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/drafts/compile-idris.pdf\">Cross-platform Compilers for Functional Languages</a> - Edwin Brady, 2015.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://eb.host.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/drafts/eff-tutorial.pdf\">Programming and Reasoning with Side-Effects in Idris</a> - Edwin Brady, 2014.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/1407/220ca09070233dca256433430d29e5321dc2.pdf\">Idris, a General Purpose Dependently Typed Programming Language: Design and Implementation</a> - Edwin Brady, 2013.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://eb.host.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/drafts/effects.pdf\">Programming and Reasoning with Algebraic Effects and Dependent Types</a> - Edwin Brady, 2013.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://eb.host.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/writings/plmms13.pdf\">Sequential decision problems, dependently typed solutions</a> - Nicola Botta, Cezar Ionescu and Edwin Brady, 2013.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://eb.host.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/writings/idris-tutorial.pdf\">Programming in Idris: a tutorial</a> - Edwin Brady, 2012.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://eb.host.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/writings/plpv11.pdf\">Idris — Systems Programming Meets Full Dependent Types</a> - Edwin Brady, 2011.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://eb.host.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/writings/icfp10.pdf\">Scrapping your Inefficient Engine: using Partial Evaluation to Improve Domain-Specific Language Implementation</a> - Edwin Brady and Kevin Hammond, 2010.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://eb.host.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/writings/fi-cbc.pdf\">Correct-by-Construction Concurrency: using Dependent Types to Verify Implementations of Effectful Resource Usage Protocols</a> - Edwin Brady and Kevin Hammond, 2010.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://eb.host.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/drafts/ngna2009-dsl.pdf\">Domain Specific Languages (DSLs) for Network Protocols</a> - Saleem Bhatti, Edwin Brady, Kevin Hammond and James McKinna, 2009.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://eb.host.cs.st-andrews.ac.uk/drafts/tfp08.pdf\">Lightweight Invariants with Full Dependent Types</a> - Edwin Brady, Christoph Herrmann and Kevin Hammond, 2008.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"presentations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#presentations\" aria-label=\"presentations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Presentations</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vkIlW797JN8\">Idris: General Purpose Programming with Dependent Types</a> - Presentation by Edwin Brady, Idris' creator.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"projects\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#projects\" aria-label=\"projects permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Projects</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/trending/idris\">GitHub's trending Idris repos</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/puffnfresh/iridium\">iridium</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/puffnfresh/iridium\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">195</span></span></a> - xmonad with the X11 abstracted and configured with Idris.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ziman/lightyear\">lightyear</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ziman/lightyear\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">224</span></span></a> - Parser combinators for Idris.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/timjb/quantities\">quantities</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/timjb/quantities\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">146</span></span></a> Type-safe physical computations and unit conversions in Idris.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/david-christiansen/idris-type-providers\">idris-type-providers</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/david-christiansen/idris-type-providers\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">76</span></span></a> - Type provider library for Idris.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/idris-hackers/IdrisScript\">IdrisScript</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/idris-hackers/IdrisScript\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">86</span></span></a> - FFI Bindings to interact with the unsafe world of JavaScript.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jfdm/idris-containers\">idris-containers</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jfdm/idris-containers\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">91</span></span></a> - Various data structures for use in the Idris Language.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/david-christiansen/IdrisSqlite\">IdrisSqlite</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/david-christiansen/IdrisSqlite\" style=\"text-decoration:n